00:17:11.210 --> 00:17:18.260
&gt;&gt; Do you talk to the author before
you write like draw the pictures,

00:17:18.260 --> 00:17:23.900
like talk to the author about what
you want to paint [inaudible]?

00:17:23.900 --> 00:17:25.660
&gt;&gt; Do I talk to the author?

00:17:25.660 --> 00:17:26.960
Usually, I don't.

00:17:26.960 --> 00:17:30.360
Usually I like to have
my own creative space

00:17:30.360 --> 00:17:31.660
to create the artwork.

00:17:31.660 --> 00:17:35.030
Sometimes the author likes to tell
me what to do but that doesn't work

00:17:35.030 --> 00:17:38.180
out because I don't get to
tell the author what to do,

00:17:38.180 --> 00:17:40.480
so they don't get to do the same.

00:17:43.190 --> 00:17:46.830
&gt;&gt; How did you come up
with the title of the book?

00:17:46.830 --> 00:17:51.070 position:56%
&gt;&gt; Well, I didn't come up with the
title for "Blue Sky" the author came

00:17:51.070 --> 00:17:52.380
up with the title for that one.

00:17:52.380 --> 00:17:55.620
But usually if I'm working on
a book, if I've written it,

00:17:55.620 --> 00:17:59.760
and I'm thinking about a title,
I try to think of something

00:17:59.760 --> 00:18:05.230
that will encompass the whole
book, that'll make sense,

00:18:05.230 --> 00:18:08.010
that'll put it all in a
nutshell and make people think

00:18:08.010 --> 00:18:11.270
about what the book might be about,

00:18:11.270 --> 00:18:13.700
something that will
grab their attention.

00:18:15.590 --> 00:18:18.000
&gt;&gt; Did you mix colors?

00:18:18.000 --> 00:18:19.770
&gt;&gt; Do I mix colors?

00:18:19.770 --> 00:18:21.890
All the time, half of
the painting is done

00:18:21.890 --> 00:18:23.190
on a palette, is mixing colors.

00:18:23.190 --> 00:18:25.490
That's half of the painting.

00:18:38.500 --> 00:18:42.060
&gt;&gt; What is your favorite book--

00:18:42.060 --> 00:18:45.480
&gt;&gt; What's my favorite
book that I've written

00:18:45.480 --> 00:18:48.630
or my favorite book of all time?

00:18:48.630 --> 00:18:50.010
&gt;&gt; When you were a kid.

00:18:50.010 --> 00:18:53.700
&gt;&gt; Oh, I really liked
"Where the Wild Things Are".

00:18:53.700 --> 00:18:56.000
That was my favorite.

00:18:57.600 --> 00:19:00.160
&gt;&gt; Where do you get
your inspiration from?

00:19:00.160 --> 00:19:04.560
&gt;&gt; I get my inspiration from
all over, something that I read,

00:19:04.560 --> 00:19:08.160
something that I might see,
from music, from an experience

00:19:08.160 --> 00:19:15.000
that I've had, everything finds
its way into the work that I do.

00:19:17.100 --> 00:19:21.610
&gt;&gt; Do you paint from
photos or real life?

00:19:21.610 --> 00:19:22.910
&gt;&gt; I do both.

00:19:22.910 --> 00:19:29.840 position:56%
Sometimes I'll take photos of myself
posing as my subject or friends

00:19:29.840 --> 00:19:36.590
or family or I'll find
photographs in books in the library

00:19:36.590 --> 00:19:42.330
or on the Internet and film,
wherever I can find it.

00:19:44.120 --> 00:19:46.660
&gt;&gt; When did you start drawing?

00:19:46.660 --> 00:19:48.100
&gt;&gt; When did I what?

00:19:48.100 --> 00:19:49.620
&gt;&gt; start drawing.

00:19:49.620 --> 00:19:50.920
&gt;&gt; When did I start drawing?

00:19:50.920 --> 00:19:53.220
I started drawing when I
was about three years old.

00:19:56.570 --> 00:19:58.780 position:56%
&gt;&gt; What was your first illustration?

00:19:58.780 --> 00:20:02.430
&gt;&gt; My first illustration, well
the first drawing I ever did was a

00:20:02.430 --> 00:20:05.860
self-portrait when I
was probably about three

00:20:05.860 --> 00:20:08.890
but it didn't really look
like me, it was pretty bad.

00:20:08.890 --> 00:20:10.560
I was new you know.

00:20:10.560 --> 00:20:14.030
&gt;&gt; What's your favorite colors?

00:20:14.030 --> 00:20:17.910
&gt;&gt; I don't have a favorite
color, I like all the colors.

00:20:19.360 --> 00:20:23.880
&gt;&gt; What year [inaudible]
you start drawing?

00:20:23.880 --> 00:20:26.850
&gt;&gt; I started drawing in 1977.

00:20:26.850 --> 00:20:29.910
He's like "that means
