00:20:35.300 --> 00:20:36.600
&gt;&gt; Who's your favorite artists?

00:20:36.600 --> 00:20:42.040
&gt;&gt; Oh, I have a lot of
artists that I really like.

00:20:42.040 --> 00:20:46.780
It's a very long list.

00:20:46.780 --> 00:20:48.620
You ever heard of John
Singer Sargent?

00:20:48.620 --> 00:20:50.520
Really like him.

00:20:50.520 --> 00:20:53.040
M.C. Wyatt.

00:20:53.040 --> 00:20:55.780
It's a very long list.

00:20:55.780 --> 00:20:58.240
Those are some of my favorites.

00:20:58.240 --> 00:21:00.710
Michelangelo, I like him too.

00:21:00.710 --> 00:21:03.420
Everybody likes him.

00:21:03.420 --> 00:21:05.550
&gt;&gt; How do you get your
ideas for your books?

00:21:05.550 --> 00:21:07.940
&gt;&gt; I think of my past experiences.

00:21:07.940 --> 00:21:11.060
When I read the words, I
see pictures, when you read,

00:21:11.060 --> 00:21:13.190 position:56%
you see pictures in your head right?

00:21:13.190 --> 00:21:15.230
You can imagine what's going on?

00:21:15.230 --> 00:21:18.390
So whatever I think about when I
read the words then I'll make a

00:21:18.390 --> 00:21:19.690
sketch of that.

00:21:19.690 --> 00:21:21.980
And if it works, great,
if it doesn't,

00:21:21.980 --> 00:21:26.480
then I have to keep working on it.

00:21:26.480 --> 00:21:31.190
&gt;&gt; How long does it
take you to decide what

00:21:31.190 --> 00:21:35.600
to incorporate into [inaudible]?

